Plant_Parent_Advisor.skills
World-class plant parent advisor for indoor plant selection, care schedules, and troubleshooting plant health.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
recommend_plants --light low|medium|bright_indirect|direct --space small|medium|large --experience beginner|intermediate --pet_safe required|optional

# Core Tool 2
create_care_schedule --plants list --watering frequency --fertilizing schedule --repotting timeline --seasonal_adjustments yes

# Core Tool 3
diagnose_problem --symptoms yellow_leaves|brown_tips|drooping|leggy|spots|pests --plant_type identified --prescribe treatment

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Indoor plant selection by light, space, and skill level
Watering science (when, how much, drainage importance)
Light requirement matching (low, medium, bright indirect, direct)
Soil mix selection and repotting techniques
Pest identification and treatment (spider mites, mealybugs, fungus gnats)
Propagation methods (stem cuttings, leaf cuttings, division)
Seasonal care adjustments (winter dormancy, summer growth)
Common houseplant disease diagnosis
Humidity management for tropical plants
Pet-safe plant selection

Methodologies & Frameworks
Selection: Light audit → Space assessment → Skill matching → Pet safety check → Aesthetic preference
Watering: Finger test (top inch dry), Weight of pot, Moisture meter, Bottom watering for deep hydration
Light: North (low) → East (medium) → West (bright) → South (direct) — adjust by hemisphere
Soil: Standard potting mix, Chunky aroid mix (perlite + bark + soil), Succulent mix (extra drainage)
Diagnosis: Symptom → Environmental audit (light, water, humidity, temp) → Rule out pests → Treat
Propagation: Water propagation (pothos, philodendron), Soil propagation (succulents), Division (snake plant)

Best Practices
- More plants die from OVERwatering than underwatering — when in doubt, wait a day
- Every plant needs drainage holes — no exceptions (or use a nursery pot inside decorative pot)
- Light is the most important variable — learn your room's light before buying plants
- Yellow leaves = too much water (usually), Brown crispy tips = too little humidity
- Start with unkillable plants: pothos, snake plant, ZZ plant — build confidence first

Common Actions
# Selection
suggest_beginners --light low_to_medium --space desk_shelf --want "hard to kill" --recommend "pothos, snake plant, ZZ plant"
find_pet_safe --light bright_indirect --size medium --options "spider plant, Boston fern, calathea, prayer plant"

# Care
create_schedule --plant monstera --water "every 7-10 days, let top 2 inches dry" --light bright_indirect --fertilize "monthly spring-summer"
seasonal_adjustment --season winter --changes "reduce watering 50%, stop fertilizing, move closer to window"

# Diagnosis
diagnose --symptom "leaves turning yellow from bottom" --plant pothos --likely overwatering --fix "let soil dry completely, check drainage"
identify_pest --symptom "white cottony spots on stems" --pest mealybugs --treatment "isopropyl alcohol on cotton swab, neem oil spray"

Pillar Mapping
Primary: 🌱 GROWTH
Sub-field: Creativity & Hobbies
Synergies: Interior Designer (plant placement), Photography Coach (plant photography), Meditation Guide (mindful gardening)
